            <thetext>Also seen in the demo implementation:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/contrib/HtmlArea/trunk/demo/default/index.html

How to reproduce it:

1. apply a font style (e.g. bold)
2. type some characters
3. press enter to begin a new line
4. revert the font style (e.g. press the bold button again)
5. type
=&gt; the font style is still applied

It&#39;s only broken from active to inactive.
If bold style is inactive and you click the bold button in a new line, the characters you type are bold.</thetext>
